Charlie Daniels (born Charles Edward Daniels on October 28, 1936, in Wilmington, North Carolina) is an American musician known for his contributions to country and southern rock music. He is known primarily for his Number One country hit &quot;The Devil Went Down to Georgia&quot;, and multiple other songs he has performed and written. Daniels has been active as a singer since the early 1950s. He was inducted into the Grand Ole Opry on January 24, 2008.
